onomic%20uncertainty%20and%20declining%20shares.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20David%20were%20taking%20on%20Goliath%20today%2C%20he%20might%20do%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-means-considering-changing-jobs-amid-rto-wfh-debate-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrom%20home%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStartups%20and%20smaller%20companies%20offering%20flexible%20work%20arrangements%20could%20better%20challenge%20larger%20rivals%20less%20willing%20to%20let%20employees%20log%20on%20from%20home%2C%20and%20many%20may%20already%20be%20doing%20so%2C%20workplace%20researchers%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20great%20way%20for%20small%20companies%20to%20compete%20with%20big%20companies%20for%20talent%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nicole%20Kyle%2C%20who%20studies%20the%20future%20of%20work%2C%20about%20giving%20workers%20greater%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENick%20Bloom%2C%20an%20economics%20professor%20at%20Stanford%20University%20who%20studies%20remote%20work%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20his%20research%20shows%20that%20in%20January%202023%2C%2027.2%25%20of%20fully%20paid%20working%20days%20were%20from%20home.%20By%20June%202025%2C%20the%20rate%20had%20edged%20up%20to%2027.9%25.%20That's%20mostly%20thanks%20to%20smaller%20companies%20and%20startups%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20comes%20as%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20names%20in%20corporate%20America%20have%20gone%20all%20in%20on%20time%20in%20the%20office.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20and%20JPMorgan%3C%2Fa%3E%20require%20five%20days%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-return-to-office-corporate-employees-4-days-a-week-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStarbucks%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20last%20week%20that%20it%20would%20bump%20its%20RTO%20mandate%20to%20four%20days%20from%20three.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20told%20BI%20that%20doing%20the%20opposite%20could%20help%20smaller%20firms%20compete%20for%20talent%20and%20cut%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20young%20workers%20focus%20on%20flexibility%20because%20juggling%20the%20demands%20of%20work%20and%20life%20tends%20to%20get%20easier%20as%20people%20age%2C%20said%20Ellen%20Ernst%20Kossek%2C%20a%20professor%20emerita%20of%20management%20at%20Purdue%20University%20who%20has%20researched%20work-life%20balance%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20decadeslong%20study%20involving%20several%20hundred%20thousand%20workers%2C%20she%20found%20that%20people%20under%2030%2C%20compared%20to%20older%20age%20groups%2C%20report%20more%20work%20and%20life%20conflict%20overall.%20That%20goes%20beyond%20family%20duties%20and%20includes%20time%20for%20exercise%2C%20domestic%20tasks%2C%20caring%20for%20pets%2C%20and%20just%20being%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224f3a1d0c-3f63-4e67-b4a8-9aa50f304c05%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn-demand%20workers%20could%20choose%20flexibility%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20across-the-board%20mandates%2C%20Kossek%20said%2C%20employers%20should%20construct%20a%20human%20resources%20strategy%20that%20accommodates%20an%20organization's%20needs%20and%20those%20of%20its%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20to%20balance%20employer%20and%20employee%20interests%2C%20or%20nobody's%20going%20to%20want%20to%20work%20for%20big%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20Kossek%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20fresh%20grads%20in%20need%20of%20mentorship%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fempty-nester-kid-college-work-boundaries-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eempty-nesters%3C%2Fa%3E%20inching%20toward%20retirement%20are%20often%20more%20inclined%20to%20enjoy%20going%20to%20the%20office%2C%20people%20of%20prime%20working%20age%20who%20are%20both%20experienced%20and%20relatively%20young%20%E2%80%94%20between%2030%20and%2050%20years%20old%20%E2%80%94%20are%20attracted%20to%20more%20flexibility%2C%20especially%20in%20tech%20industries%2C%20Stanford's%20Bloom%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomeone%20leaving%20school%20with%20a%20master's%20degree%20in%20computer%20science%20and%20a%20specialty%20in%20AI%20would%20fall%20into%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-talent-wars-recruiting-hiring-white-hot-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehottest%20talent%20pools%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20If%20the%20grad%20had%20competing%20job%20offers%20and%20one%20employer%20allowed%20someone%20to%20work%20from%20home%20twice%20a%20week%20and%20one%20didn't%2C%20it%20would%20likely%20be%20an%20easy%20choice%2C%20Bloom%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20caregiving%20responsibilities%20more%20often%20fall%20to%20women%20than%20men%2C%20rigid%20RTO%20requirements%20tend%20to%20lead%20to%20a%20paucity%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcost-of-inequity-america-lack-women-ceos-huge-financial-problem-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewomen%20in%20the%20upper%20ranks%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20some%20prestige%20industries%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20pretty%20hard%20to%20argue%20that%20having%2090%25%20men%20in%20a%20firm%20is%20great%20for%20business%2C%20which%20is%20the%20case%20for%20many%20tech%20and%20finance%20companies%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Bloom%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221e75718b-0251-47a5-9973-86c048fd6541%5C%22%3EBig%20businesses%20are%20under%20pressure%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20year%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-trump-tariff-uncertainty-affecting-businesses-spending-prices-hiring-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etariff%20whiplash%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20businesses%20are%20facing%20rising%20costs%2C%20and%20remote%20work%20can%20be%20an%20easy%20scapegoat%20for%20l