tesy%20of%20Melissa%20Shaw%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMelissa%20Shaw%20became%20her%20mother's%20primary%20caregiver%20after%20a%20sudden%20terminal%20cancer%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShaw%2C%20a%20financial%20advisor%2C%20learned%20crucial%20lessons%20about%20end-of-life%20planning%20and%20caregiving.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHer%20biggest%20lessons%20include%20the%20importance%20of%20Medigap%2C%20healthcare%20proxies%2C%20and%20life%20insurance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Melissa%20Shaw%2C%20a%2046-year-old%20financial%20advisor%20in%20Palo%20Alto%2C%20California.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20a%20financial%20advisor%20since%202011%20and%20have%20worked%20at%20Teachers%20Insurance%20and%20Annuity%20Association%20of%20America%2C%20or%20TIAA%2C%20as%20a%20wealth%20management%20advisor%20for%20over%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20help%20clients%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-in-estate-planning-it-makes-me-appreciate-my-family-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eestate%20and%20incapacity%20planning%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20I%20encountered%20completely%20different%20issues%20when%20my%20own%20mother%20became%20terminally%20ill%20and%20I%20became%20her%20primary%20caregiver%20in%20October%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20diagnosis%20was%20sudden.%20Doctors%20found%20stage%20four%20cancer%20that%20had%20metastasized%20to%20her%20back%2C%20causing%20a%20fracture.%20Within%20weeks%2C%20my%20family%20moved%20her%20from%20Las%20Vegas%20to%20Northern%20California%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20died%20by%20the%20end%20of%20December%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20a%20two-month%20ordeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222381ce55-018f-4163-8f53-420c21fdc777%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBecoming%20her%20caregiver%20was%20emotionally%20intense%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20she%20seemed%20fine%2C%20but%20she%20declined%20rapidly.%20It%20was%20shocking%20and%20unexpected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20visited%20the%20hospital%20daily%20and%20took%20on%20the%20bulk%20of%20decision-making%20responsibilities.%20Thankfully%2C%20TIAA%20offers%20generous%20caregiver%20benefits%20and%20flexibility%2C%20and%20I%20had%20savings%20to%20help%20cover%20unexpected%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20learned%20many%20valuable%20lessons%20through%20this%20experience%20about%20end-of-life%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22da7ca24f-3452-4936-b4a7-cdca05a5f283%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Medicare%20supplemental%20plans%20are%20essential%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20enrolling%20in%20Medicare%20at%20the%20age%20of%2065%2C%20my%20mom%20opted%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-medigap-plans-cost-every-state-ranked-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMedigap%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Medicare%20Supplement%20Insurance)%20plan%20instead%20of%20a%20Medicare%20Advantage%20plan%2C%20and%20that%20decision%20proved%20vital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20Medigap%20plan%20covered%2020%25%20of%20medical%20costs%20that%20original%20Medicare%20didn't%2C%20including%20any%20doctor%20or%20procedure%20approved%20by%20Medicare%2C%20without%20referrals%20or%20prior%20authorizations.%20Every%20doctor%20she%20saw%20was%20relieved%20she%20had%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20or%20a%20loved%20one%20is%20approaching%2065%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20with%20ongoing%20health%20issues%20%E2%80%94%20I%20strongly%20recommend%20researching%20Medigap%20options%20during%20the%20Medigap%20Open%20Enrollment%20Period%2C%20when%20insurers%20can't%20deny%20coverage%20or%20charge%20more%20due%20to%20pre-existing%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228ffe110b-28f6-4bd3-80b4-35a3f662c41c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Assign%20a%20designated%20healthcare%20decision-maker%20ASAP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%20didn't%20assign%20a%20designated%20decision-maker%2C%20and%20I%20couldn't%20make%20health%20decisions%20for%20her.%20When%20her%20health%20rapidly%20declined%20in%20the%20last%20three%20weeks%20of%20her%20life%2C%20she%20became%20barely%20cognizant%20and%20luckily%20was%20able%20to%20manage%20a%20scribbled%20signature%20for%20a%20necessary%20procedure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20to%20prepare%20a%20POA%20and%20healthcare%20proxy%2C%20but%20by%20the%20time%20it%20was%20ready%2C%20she%20was%20no%20longer%20mentally%20competent%20enough%20to%20sign%20it.%20She%20signed%20an%20advanced%20directive%20form%20with%20the%20hospital%20when%20she%20started%20the%20cancer%20treatment%2C%20which%20allowed%20me%20to%20make%20some%20decisions%20on%20her%20behalf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20how%20imperative%20it%20is%20to%20name%20a%20health%20proxy%20at%20any%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b013b244-3bb5-4f47-abf9-058a964c8848%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Banking%20may%20not%20be%20easily%20accessible%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20she%20died%2C%20we%20were%20unable%20to%20access%20her%20bank%20account%20funds%20for%2045%20days%20due%20to%20a%20waiting%20period%20intended%20to%20protect%20creditors.%20Luckily%2C%20she%20had%20a%20term%20life%20insurance%20policy%20that%20paid%20out%20quickly%20to%20help%20cover%20immediate%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20she%20didn't%20name%20a%20beneficiary%20for%20the%20bank%20accounts%2C%20which%20is%20a%20common%20mistake.%20Many%20assume%20that%20checking%20accounts%20don't%20need%20beneficiaries%2C%20but%20even%20modest%20balances%20may%20end%20up%20in%20probate%2C%20which%20can%20be%20a%20significant%20hassle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20the%20bank%20was%20unable%20to%20share%20her%20transaction%20history%2C%20so%20I%20had%20no%20way%20of%20knowing%20which%20bills%20had%20already%20been%20paid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a1e77a69-b690-4510-b6d3-789f57183eac%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Sign%20up%20for%20life%20insurance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20received%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flife-insurance%2Fbest-life-insurance-companies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elife%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20proceeds%20quickly%3B%20all%20that%20was%20required%20was%20a%20death%20certificate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClients%20may%20want%20to%20consider%20insurance%20as%20a%20liquidity%20measure%20at%20death%20to%20cover%20immediate%20expenses%2C%20such%20as%20funeral%20costs%20and%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ef9a7546-09f0-4ba3-bb36-569fcf803aca%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Prepare%20for%20end-of-life%20costs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20surprised%20by%20how%20expensive%20it%20is%20to%20bury%20someone.%20We%20were%20quoted%20up%20to%20%2425%2C000%20for%20burial%20plots%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20cremation%2C%20which%20we%20chose%2C%20came%20to%20around%20%2423%2C000%20after%20including%20the%20niche%20(a%20final%20resting%20spot%20to%20house%20cremated%20remains)%20and%20the%20funeral.%20Prepaying%20or%20researching%20in%20advance%20can%20prevent%20financial%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220a0610bb-c586-404f-bca3-ad881524ab80%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Prepare%20for%20the%20difficulties%20of%20caretaking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20many%20nights%20in%20the%20hospital%20with%20my%20mom.%20Her%20condition%20changed%20from%20day%20to%20day%3B%20it%20was%20an%20emotional%20roller%20coaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBalancing%20work%2C%20caregiving%2C%20and%20my%20own%20emotional%20health%20was%20difficult.%20I'm%20married%2C%20and%20my%20kids%20were%205%20and%207%20years%20old.%20I%20wasn't%20seeing%20them%20regularly%20during%20the%20two%20months%20she%20was%20sick.%20Luckily%2C%20TIAA%20offered%20eight%20weeks%20of%20caregiver%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20caregivers%20only%20have%20access%20to%20unpaid%20leave%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A