ng%20a%20lot%20of%20revenue%2C%20but%20the%20profit%20margin%20was%20so%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20biggest%20expenses%20were%20paying%20staff%20%E2%80%94%20our%20security%2C%20actors%2C%20greeters%2C%20DJs%2C%20band%20performers%2C%20and%20cleanup%20crew.%20The%20second%20biggest%20cost%20was%20alcohol%20and%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20so%20green%20and%20inexperienced%2C%20and%20we%20didn't%20really%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-create-a-business-budget-to-grow-your-company%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehave%20a%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20didn't%20know%20what%20we'd%20made%20until%20three%20months%20after%20the%20events%20had%20finished.%20We%20barely%20made%20anything%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0just%20a%20few%20thousand%20dollars%20after%20over%20a%20dozen%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20hard%20business.%20It%20was%20stressful%20and%20ended%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-partnership-ended-friendship-partners-friends-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edestroying%20my%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20my%20girlfriend.%20We%20were%20constantly%20monitoring%20who%20was%20doing%20what%20and%20figuring%20out%20which%20tasks%20were%20more%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20that%20I%20don't%20ever%20want%20a%20cofounder%20again%3B%20when%20someone%20else%20has%20veto%20power%20over%20your%20business%2C%20it'll%20never%20be%20100%25%20equal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220b27d864-673e-4aee-8d19-ed3606d0b5d5%5C%22%3EI%20pivoted%20back%20into%20the%20corporate%20world%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20six%20months%2C%20I%20chose%20to%20return%20to%20a%20career%20working%20for%20someone%20else%20%E2%80%94%20this%20time%20in%20tech.%20I%20held%20C-level%20roles%20at%20several%20startups%2C%20and%20my%20last%20role%20was%20Chief%20of%20Staff%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftried-calm-app-month-panic-disorder-meditation-2021-5%5C%22%20target