gh%20the%20Cognition%20deal%20appears%20to%20be%20far%20lower%20than%20what%20OpenAI%20originally%20offered.%20Three%20sources%20estimated%20Cognition%2C%20which%20itself%20is%20only%20worth%20%244%20billion%2C%20paid%20about%20%24300%20million%20in%20stock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpokespeople%20for%20Windsurf%20and%20Google%20declined%20to%20comment.%20Varun%20Mohan%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20Windsurf%20who%20is%20now%20part%20of%20Google%3B%20Scott%20Wu%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Cognition%3B%20and%20Jeff%20Wang%2C%20Windsurf's%20new%20CEO%2C%20all%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fcognition_labs%2Fstatus%2F1944819486538023138%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECognition%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3B100%25%20of%20Windsurf%20employees%20will%20participate%20financially%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20deal%20and%20%26quot%3Bthey%20will%20also%20have%20all%20vesting%20cliffs%20waived%20and%20will%20receive%20fully%20accelerated%20vesting%20for%20their%20work%20to%20date.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last-ditch%20deal%20was%20a%20far%20better%20outcome%20for%20employees%20than%20many%20feared%20after%20the%20Google%20acquisition%2C%20but%20some%20VCs%20feel%20that%20the%20transaction%20sets%20a%20dangerous%20precedent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20pretty%20sad%20place%20to%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Deedy%20Das%2C%20an%20investor%20at%20Menlo%20Ventures.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20join%20a%20company%2C%20you%20expect%20decisions%20to%20be%20made%20together%2C%20so%20this%20does%20have%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20founding%20team%20members.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWindsurf%20and%20others%20are%20really%20bad%20examples%20of%20founders%20leaving%20their%20teams%20behind%20and%20not%20even%20sharing%20the%20proceeds%20with%20their%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fvkhosla%2Fstatus%2F1946655439921557760%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20storied%20investor%20Vinod%20Khosla%20on%20X.%20%26quot%3BI%20definitely%20would%20not%20work%20with%20their%20founders%20next%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraditionally%2C%20early%20employees%20are%20willing%20to%20accept%20less%20cash%20and%20more%20equity%20while%20working%20100-hour%20weeks%20in%20the%20hope%20that%20they%20will%20share%20in%20the%20upside%20should%20their%20company%20be%20acquired%20someday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20an%20exit%20can%20happen%20and%20you%20don't%20participate%20in%20it%2C%20that's%20pretty%20bad%20for%20startup%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Masad.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20broadly%20bad%20for%20the%20startup%20ecosystem%20for%20these%20deals%20to%20be%20financially%20engineered%20in%20this%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Google%20deal%2C%20Masad%20took%20to%20X%20to%20offer%20an%20olive%20branch%2C%20inviting%20Windsurf%20employees%20to%20decamp%20to%20Replit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20were%20part%20of%20Windsurf%20and%20got%20left%20behind%2C%20we'd%20like%20to%20talk%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Famasad%2Fstatus%2F1944220905053598210%3Fs%3D46%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20wrote.%20%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20passed%20on%20many%20acquisitions%20over%20the%20years%2C%20and%20any%20liquidity%20has%20always%20included%20employees.%26quot%3B%20(Masad%20said%20he's%20still%20having%20%26quot%3Bconversations%26quot%3B%20with%20some%20employees%2C%20but%20most%20have%20chosen%20to%20go%20to%20Cognition.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Windsurf%20investors%20have%20also%20been%20critical%20of%20the%20deal.%20While%20they%20are%20happy%20to%20get%20some%20return%20on%20their%20investment%2C%20it's%20hardly%20the%20venture-style%20outcome%20they%20hoped%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%20that%20the%20company%20technically%20didn't%20actually%20fully%20realize%20that%20decacorn%20potential%2C%20which%20was%20the%20reason%20we%20invested%20in%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Krish%20Ramadurai%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20AIX%20Ventures%2C%20referring%20to%20a%20startup%20worth%20more%20than%20%2410%20billion.%3Cstrong%3E%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20would've%20preferred%20to%20just%20take%20a%20clean%20exit%20from%20OpenAI.%20That%20was%20a%20nice%2C%20very%20simple%20acquisition.%20Now%20this%20is%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20fucking%20mess.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERamadurai%20is%20also%20unsettled%20by%20what%20the%20deal%20means%20for%20the%20future%20of%20the%20company%20and%20its%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20mojo%20gets%20thrown%20in%20the%20blender%2C%26quot%3B%20Ramadurai%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20key%20leaders%20and%20the%20engineers%20that%20get%20poached%20are%20all%20stoked%2C%20but%20everybody%20else%20that's%20left%20behind%20is%20in%20this%20weird%20purgatory%20situation%20because%20they%20have%20to%20maintain%20the%20momentum%20even%20though%20they%20lost%20the%20key%20talent%20in%20the%20leadership.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222a176ea0-cf50-4495-9df1-9ed8dbe4ca02%5C%22%3EMore%20similar%20deals%20to%20come%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20happened%20at%20Windsurf%20follows%20other%20unusually%20structured%20deals%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharacter-ai-chatbot-teen-suicide-lawsuit-google-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECharacter%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-hired-inflection-team-amid-board-concerns-about-openai-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EInflection%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-scale-ai-15-billion-alexandr-wang-acquihire-ai-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EScale%20AI%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20avoided%20outright%20acquiring%20a%20company%20in%20order%20to%20gain%20access%20to%20its%20founders%20and%20top%20AI%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20Scale%20AI%2C%20Meta%20paid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-scale-ai-15-billion-alexandr-wang-acquihire-ai-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%2414%20billion%20for%20a%2049%20percent%20stake%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20data%20labeling%20company%20and%20hired%20its%20founder%2C%20Alexandr%20Wang%2C%20to%20run%20its%20Superintelligence%20group.%20Meta%20also%20hired%20some%20of%20the%20startup's%20researchers.%20Last%20week%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscale-ai-layoffs-citing-overhiring-unprofitability-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EScale%20AI%20laid%20off%2014%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20workforce%2C%20or%20200%20employees%2C%20and%20revealed%20it%20is%20unprofitable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20transaction%20is%20different%2C%20and%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Windsurf%2C%20the%20company%20was%20not%20seen%20as%20having%20conventionally%20elite%20AI%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGoogle%20sees%20Windsurf%20as%20an%20autonomous%20software%20engineer%20%E2%80%94an%20AI%20that's%20as%20productive%20as%20an%20elite%20full-stack%20team%2C%20or%20maybe%20even%20a%20department%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Danny%20Pantuso%2C%20an%20investor%20at%20Mucker%20Capital.%20%26quot%3BThrough%20that%20lens%2C%20Google's%20license%20fee%20resembles%20an%20upfront%20payment%20for%20permanent%20access%20to%20this%20capability%2C%20similar%20to%20Microsoft's%20deal%20with%20OpenAI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20all%20these%20deals%20have%20in%20common%20is%20that%20they%20can%20close%20quickly%20and%20avoid%20regulatory%20scrutiny%20%E2%80%94%20two%20benefits%20that%20mean%20this%20type%20of%20transaction%20is%20only%20going%20to%20become%20more%20common%2C%20according%20to%20Steve%20Brotman%2C%20managing%20partner%20at%20Alpha%20Partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3EThis%20isn't%20a%20one-off%2C%20it's%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20pattern%20where%20Big%20Tech%20hedges%20its%20bets%2C%26quot%3B%20