%20chief%20of%20public%20policy%20at%20the%20Canadian%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20look%20back%20on%20this%20in%2020%20years%2C%20I%20hope%20to%20be%20able%20to%20say%20that%20this%20woke%20Canada%20up%20to%20the%20need%20to%20be%20a%20little%20more%20strategic%20and%20have%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20of%20its%20own%20agency%20in%20the%20economy%20and%20in%20the%20kind%20of%20economy%20we%20want.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20US%20doesn't%20want%20to%20be%20as%20good%20of%20friends%20anymore%2C%20fine%2C%20Canada%20can%20make%20new%2C%20better%20friends%2C%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20Canadian%20economies%20are%20deeply%20intertwined.%20A%20shared%20language%2C%20geographic%20proximity%2C%20and%20interconnected%20supply%20chains%20have%20made%20the%20countries%20convenient%20strategic%20partners%20for%20decades.%20Three-quarters%20of%20Canada's%20exports%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fustr.gov%2Fcountries-regions%2Famericas%2Fcanada%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ego%20to%20the%20United%20States%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20nearly%20half%20of%20its%20imported%20goods%20come%20from%20the%20US.%20In%202024%2C%20Canada%20was%20the%20third-largest%20source%20of%20imports%20to%20the%20US%2C%20behind%20China%20and%20Mexico.%20Canada%20was%20also%20the%20top%20destination%20for%20exports%20from%20the%20US.%20Several%20of%20the%20two%20countries'%20biggest%20industries%2C%20including%20automotives%20and%20energy%2C%20are%20highly%20interwoven%20with%20one%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20belligerent%20stance%20toward%20Canada%20has%20thrown%20the%20country%20for%20a%20loop.%20While%20Canada%20isn't%20subject%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-house-says-trumps-baseline-10-tariff-here-to-stay-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E10%25%20blanket%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20he's%20placed%20on%20imports%20from%20other%20countries%2C%20he's%20targeted%20specific%20areas%20with%20import%20taxes%2C%20including%2050%25%20tariffs%20on%20steel%20and%20aluminum%2C%2025%25%20tariffs%20on%20cars%2C%2010%25%20tariffs%20on%20potash%20and%20energy%2C%20and%2025%25%20tariffs%20on%20imports%20not%20compliant%20with%20the%20US-Mexico-Canada%20trade%20deal%20(formerly%20known%20as%20NAFTA).%20He's%20also%20planning%20to%20place%20a%2050%25%20tariff%20on%20copper%20come%20August.%20Most%20recently%2C%20the%20president%20threatened%20to%20put%20a%2035%25%20tariff%20on%20imports%20from%20Canada%2C%20blaming%20its%20retaliatory%20tariffs%20for%20the%20move%2C%20though%20it%20wasn't%20immediately%20clear%20what%20goods%20this%20would%20apply%20to.%20(The%20president%20says%20this%20is%20about%20fentanyl%2C%20though%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbp.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fstats%2Fdrug-seizure-statistics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Every%20little%20fentanyl%3C%2Fa%3E%20comes%20to%20the%20US%20over%20the%20Canadian%20border.)%20A%20Trump%20administration%20official%20said%20in%20an%20email%20that%20they%20expected%20goods%20currently%20tariffed%20at%2025%25%20to%20go%20up%20to%2035%25%2C%20though%20no%20final%20decisions%20have%20been%20made%20by%20the%20president.%20Given%20Trump's%20persistent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-mexico-canada-tariffs-economic-uncertainty-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eflip-flopping%20on%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20not%20clear%20whether%20they%20will%20actually%20take%20hold.%20This%20constant%20state%20of%20flux%20is%20making%20investors%2C%20at%20the%20very%20least%2C%20a%20bit%20more%20casual%20about%20the%20whole%20thing.%20The%20foreign%20exchange%20market%2C%20which%20tracks%20currency%20fluctuations%2C%20would%20indicate%20investors%20aren't%20too%20worried%20about%20it%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Canadian%20dollar%20isn't%20swinging%20based%20on%20Trump's%20pronouncements%20and%20has%20strengthened%20in%20recent%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20market%2C%20so%20to%20speak%2C%20is%20seeing%20through%20a%20lot%20of%20this%20rabble-rousing%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Peter%20Morrow%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaco-trade-trump-tariffs-investors-stock-market-japan-south-korea-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETACO%20trade%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20short%20for%20Trump%20Always%20Chickens%20Out%20and%20proxy%20for%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20president%20backs%20down%20from%20his%20most%20aggressive%20threats%20%E2%80%94%20is%20alive%20in%20the%20Great%20White%20North%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%2C%20the%20American%20president's%20trade%20antics%20are%20taking%20a%20toll%20on%20Canada.%20It's%20the%20country%20most%20hurt%20by%20the%20US%20trade%20war%20so%20far%20%E2%80%94%20the%20US%20is%20second.%20An%20analysis%20from%20the%20Yale%20Budget%20Lab%20found%20Trump's%20tariffs%20and%20Canadian%20countermeasures%20could%20cause%20Canada's%20economy%20to%20shrink%20by%202.1%25%20in%20the%20long%20term.%20The%20trade%20dispute%20increases%20the%20chances%20of%20a%20recession%20in%20Canada%2C%20and%20it%20threatens%20to%20increase%20inflation.%20It%20also%20injects%20an%20incredible%20amount%20of%20uncertainty%20into%20the%20economy.%20It's%20next%20to%20impossible%20for%20Canadian%20businesses%20to%20plan%20for%20the%20future%20when%20they%20have%20no%20idea%20what%20the%20guy%20in%20the%20White%20House%20is%20going%20to%20do%2C%20day-to-day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20only%20the%20tariff%20wall%3B%20it's%20kind%20of%20a%20wall%20of%20uncertainty%20that's%20going%20up%20between%20the%20two%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Julian%20Karaguesian%2C%20a%20course%20lecturer%20in%20McGill%20University's%20economics%20department.%20%26quot%3BThe%20immediate%20effect%20it's%20having%20in%20the%20short%20term%20is%20a%20cooling%20effect%20on%20business%20investment%2C%20which%20is%20the%20dynamic%20part%20of%20the%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ECanada%20isn't%20taking%20the%20economic%20punch%20in%20the%20face%20lying%20down.%20Canada's%20new%20prime%20minister%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-election-results-mark-carney-trump-trade-war-pierre-poilievre-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMark%20Carney%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20Canadian%20public%20have%20taken%20a%20hockey-esque%20%26quot%3Belbows%20up%26quot%3B%20approach%20to%20the%20US.%20A%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-turn-local-products-trump-tariffs-mislabeling-complaints-surge-fraud-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBuy%20Canadian%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20movement%20has%20swept%20the%20nation.%20Canadians%20are%20swapping%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanadian-stores-labeling-american-imports-consumers-responding-patriotism-trump-tariffs-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmerican-made%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20groceries%20for%20national%20ones%2C%20guided%20by%20forums%20and%20apps%20that%20help%20distinguish%20locally%20made%20goods%20from%20their%20Yankee%20counterparts.%20Liquor%20stores%20have%20pulled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbourbon-whiskey-tariffs-europe-canada-trump-trade-war-prices-cost-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20whiskeys%3C%2Fa%3E%20off%20the%20shelves.%20Instead%20of%20going%20to%20McDonald's%2C%20Canadians%20are%20hitting%20up%20A%26amp%3BW.%20They're%20opening%20up%20the%20CBC%20Gem%20streaming%20app%20to%20see%20what's%20on%20there%20instead%20of%20Netflix.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBrand%20damage%20can%20last%20a%20long%20time.%20People%20won't%20remember%20in%2010%20years%20why%20they%20don't%20like%20Nike%20anymore%2C%20but%20they%20will%20still%20think%20slightly%20ill%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20guy%20who%20runs%20a%20website%20called%20Shop%20Canadian%20Stuff%20tells%20me.%20He%20spoke%20with%20me%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20because%20his%20job%20doesn't%20know%20about%20his%20nationalist%20side%20hustle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvan%20Worman%2C%20one%20of%20the%20moderators%20of%20a%20Buy%20Canadian%20subreddit%2C%20tells%20me%20that%20Canadians%20redirecting%20their%20purchasing%20power%20is%20a%20loss%20for%20the%20US%20because%20it's%20opening%20people's%20eyes%20to%20the%20quality%20of%20non-American%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20going%20to%20find%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20products%20that%20are%20getting%20imported%20from%20Europe%20have%20better%20safety%20standards%2C%20have%20higher%20quality%20control%20than%20the%20US%2C%20and%20it%20doesn't%20come%20with%20all%20the%20hang-ups%20and%20baggage%20of%20buying%20from%20somebody%20who%20wants%20to%20invade%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20Worman%20is%20originally%20from%20Alaska%20and%20has%20lived%20in%20Canada%20for%20a%20decade.%20When%20people%20don't%20realize%20he's%20not%20Canadian%2C%20he%20doesn't%20correct%20them.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20genuinely%20very%20angry%20at%20us%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20attacks%20are%20also%20fostering%20a%20willingness%20to%20reshape%20the%20domestic%20Canadian%20economy%3A%20Local%20governments%20are%20getting%20rid%20of%20internal%20trade%20barriers%20that%20have%20prevented%20goods%20from%20flowing%20between%20provinces.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20had%2C%20for%20decades%2C%20stupid%2C%20unnecessary%20rules%20between%20Canadian%20provinces%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dan%20Kelly%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Canadian%20Federation%20of%20Independent%20Business.%20%26quot%3BThere%20has%20been%20a%20resurgence%20of%20that%20among%20our%20members%20that%20are%20now%20saying%2C%20'Well%2C%20wait%20a%20minute%2C%20if%20the%20US%20market%20is%20uncertain%2C%20then%20I'll%20send%20my%20goods%20to%20Ontario%20rather%20than%20to%20New%20York.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20government%20says%20knocking%20down%20interprovincial%20trade%20restrictions%20could%20boost%20Canada's%20economy%20by%20%24200%20billion%20annually.%20Karaguesian%20believes%20that%20may%20be%20an%20overstatement%2C%20but%20that%20and%20the%20domestic%20focus%20are%20emblematic%20of%20a%20bigger%20shift.%20%26quot%3BThe%20people%20that%20are%20running%20the%20United%20States%20are%20saying%20we%20don't%20really%20have%20any%20allies%20right%20now%20%E2%80%94%20we%20have%20adversaries%2C%20and%20we%20have%20countries%20we%20can%20tell%20what%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20making%20the%20emphasis%20on%20a%20more%20unified%20Canadian%20economy%20all%20the%20more%20important%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20on%20the%20shorter-term%20front%2C%20many%20Canadian%20businesses%20that%20hadn't%20yet%20bothered%20to%20get%20compliant%20with%20the%20US-Mexico-Canada%20Agreement%20because%20previous%20tariff%20levels%20were%20so%20negligible%20are%20getting%20their%20ducks%20in%20a%20row.%20Holmes%2C%20from%20the%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%2C%20says%20that%20pre-Trump%2C%20only%20about%20half%20of%20the%20products%20crossing%20the%20border%20were%20USMCA%20compliant%2C%20because%20companies%20hadn't%20bothered%20to%20do%20the%20paperwork%2C%20but%20over%20the%20past%20four%20months%2C%20that's%20gotten%20to%20about%20two-thirds.%20He%20estimates%20that%2090%25%20of%20Canadian%20products%20should%20be%20compliant%20overall%20but%20notes%20that%20%26quot%3Bit's%20just%20the%20work%20of%20getting%20it%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECanadian%20companies%20aren't%20rushing%20to%20move%20their%20operations%20to%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20which%20seems%20to%20be%2C%20in%20large%20part%2C%20Trump's%20goal%20in%20all%20of%20this%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20are%20adapting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20diversifying%20their%20sales%2C%20and%20they're%20diversifying%20their%20suppliers%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Patrick%20Gill%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20the%20Business%20Data%20Lab%20at%20the%20Canadian%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20they're%20looking%20to%20other%20international%20markets%20where%20Canada%20has%20established%20free%20trade%20agreements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States'%20attitudes%20have%20sent%20Canada%20seeking%20improved%20trade%20agreements%20and%20relations%20elsewhere%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapparel-maker-anian-trade-war-strengthening-canadas-ties-europe-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EEurope%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Asia%2C%20and%20the%20Global%20South.%20In%20an%20attempt%20to%20wean%20itself%20off%20the%20US%2C%20Canada%20is%20looking%20to%20expand%20where%20it%20sources%20from%20and%20where%20it%20sells.%20But%20just%20how%20far%20to%20go%20is%20a%20difficult%20calculation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20people%20say%20that%20Canada%20should%20take%20the%20easy%20win%2C%20stay%20linked%20to%20the%20US%2C%20and%20just%20ride%20it%20out.%20And%20there's%20other%20people%20who%20say%20that%20the%20United%20States%20is%20not%20a%20reliable%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhats-complicating-trumps-trade-talks-rice-tech-and-china-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etrading%20partner%3C%2Fa%3E%20anymore%2C%20and%20that%20Canada%20should%20strengthen%20its%20relationships%20with%20other%20countries.%20But%20developing%20those%20other%20relationships%20is%20not%20easy%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Morrow%2C%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECanada%20may%20be%20at%20its%20breaking%20point.%20Canadian%20political%20leaders%20and%20nationals%20feel%20like%20the%20US%20will%20never%20be%20satisfied%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-digital-tax-cost-us-tech-giants-billions-each-year-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20matter%20how%20much%20ground%20they%20give%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20find%20the%2051st%20state%20jokes%20really%20offensive.%20And%20as%20much%20as%20the%20US-Canada%20relationship%20is%20extra%20strained%20right%20now%2C%20Canadians%20have%20long%20been%20skeptical%20of%20their%20larger%20neighbors.%20The%20US-Canada%20free%20trade%20agreement%20that%20predated%20NAFTA%20in%20the%20late%201980s%20was%20unpopular%20in%20Canada.%20Post-9%2F11%2C%20Canada%20resisted%20pressure%20from%20the%20US%20to%20join%20the%20Iraq%20invasion%20and%20chafed%20at%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush's%20%26quot%3Byou're%20with%20us%20or%20against%20us%26quot%3B%20mentality.%20Some%20Canadian%20policymakers%20felt%20slighted%20by%20the%20Obama%20administration's%20attempts%20at%20pushing%20%26quot%3BBuy%20American%26quot%3B%20provisions%20and%20by%20the%20US-focused%20investments%20in%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-inflation-reduction-act-means-finances-tax-health-climate-democrats-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInflation%20Reduction%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20US%20and%20Canada%20have%20long%20grumbled%20over%20dairy%20and%20lumber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCanada%20has%20a%20strong%20skepticism%20of%20the%20US%20even%20during%20the%20best%20of%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20Morrow%20says%2C%20citing%20a%20quote%20from%20former%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20Pierre%20Trudeau%20(Justin's%20father)%2C%20who%20said%20living%20next%20to%20the%20US%20was%20like%20%26quot%3Bsleeping%20with%20an%20elephant%20%E2%80%94%20no%20matter%20how%20friendly%20or%20even-tempered%20is%20the%20beast%2C%20if%20one%20can%20call%20it%20that%2C%20one%20is%20affected%20by%20every%20twitch%20and%20grunt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20United%20States%2C%20for%20its%20entire%20history%2C%20has%20been%20a%20protectionist%20country%20except%20the%20time%20from%20the%20attack%20on%20Pearl%20Harbor%20in%201941%20to%20the%209%2F11%20attacks%2C%26quot%3B%20Karaguesian%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20United%20States%20was%20the%20biggest%20defender%20of%20free%20trade%20at%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20century%20because%20they%20were%20winning%20at%20that%20game.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20says%20the%20US%20has%20%26quot%3Ball%20the%20cards%26quot%3B%20in%20trade%20relations%20with%20Canada.%20The%20US%20certainly%20has%20%3Cem%3Emore%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecards%2C%20but%20Canada%20isn't%20playing%20with%20an%20empty%20hand.%20The%20country%20has%20felt%20emboldened%20to%20strengthen%20trade%20relations%20with%20other%20partners%2C%20to%20revive%20its%20own%20manufacturing%20base%2C%20and%20to%20separate%20itself%20economically%2C%20culturally%2C%20and%20otherwise%20from%20the%20US.%20Kelly%2C%20from%20CFIB%2C%20compares%20Canada's%20retaliatory%20tariffs%20to%20economic%20chemotherapy%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Byou%20take%20the%20poison%20in%20order%20to%20try%20to%20fight%20the%20larger%20battle%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20adds%20that%20it%20says%20something%20that%20the%20country%20is%20so%20willing%20to%20dig%20in.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20fairly%20significant%20resolve%20among%20Canadian%20businesses%20to%20press%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20Trump's%20trade%20war%20is%20doing%20real%20damage%20to%20Canada%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20it%20should%20be%20said%2C%20to%20the%20US.%20Continuing%20the%20tit-for-tat%20won't%20mean%20mutually%20assured%20destruction%20for%20the%20neighboring%20countries%2C%20but%20it%20is%20one%20that%20will%20harm%20both%2C%20even%20if%20to%20different%20degrees.%20Canada's%2040%20million%20population%20can't%20replace%20the%20US's%20340%20million%20in%20terms%20of%20a%20consumer%20market.%20It%20will%20continue%20to%20depend%20on%20the%20US%20and%2C%20increasingly%2C%20others%20for%20commerce%20and%20trade.%20And%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20complete%20decoupling%20is%20quite%20unfathomable%2C%20unless%20Americans%20want%20to%20spend%20a%20ton%20more%20on%20energy%20and%20the%20entire%20North%20American%20auto%20sector%20is%20overhauled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3